The Akwa Ibom State Task Force on Implementation of Quarantine And Restriction of Movement Regulation 2020 led by the State Commissioner of Police, Mr Imohime Edgal, on Sunday during a routine surveillance stopped over at Hilltop of Glory Covenant Ministry Intl., St. Patrick’s Catholic Church, Afaha Inang and Methodist Church Nigeria, Obio Etoi Circuit within Uyo metropolis and dismissed worshippers who defied the social gathering order to attend service. Addressing the worshipers Edgar warned them   to desist from flouting the restriction of movement and social gathering order stressing that the people must be healthy and free from the Coronavirus disease to observe their religious obligations. He said the task force will continue in its onerous  of protecting the citizens by educating church leaders on the need to respect the stay at home order and any worshiper  caught will have himself  or herself to blame.